What is Ansible?

Open-source Configuration Management + Automation tool.

Written in Python, uses YAML (playbooks).

Agentless â†’ connects via SSH/WinRM.

Idempotent â†’ same playbook can be run multiple times safely.

Core Concepts

Inventory â†’ list of hosts (static or dynamic).

Playbook â†’ YAML file with tasks.

Play â†’ mapping between hosts & tasks.

Task â†’ single unit of work (install pkg, copy file).

Module â†’ building block (yum, apt, service, copy, template).

Ad-Hoc Commands â†’ quick one-liners (not playbooks).

Facts â†’ system properties gathered by Ansible.

Basic Commands

ansible all -m ping -i inventory.ini
ansible-playbook -i inventory.ini playbook.yml
ansible-doc -l        # list modules
ansible-galaxy init myrole


âœ… Foundation knowledge for every DevOps engineer.

ğŸ”¹ 2ï¸âƒ£ Medium-Level Concepts (Practical DevOps Usage)

Inventory

Static â†’ INI/YAML file.

Dynamic â†’ pull from AWS/GCP/Azure APIs.

Groups â†’ [webservers], [dbservers].

Host vars â†’ host_vars/, group_vars/.

Variables

Precedence order (highest to lowest):
command-line vars â†’ playbook vars â†’ role vars â†’ inventory vars â†’ defaults.

Types: host vars, group vars, vars_files, registered vars.

Facts â†’ auto-collected system info (ansible_facts).

Templates (Jinja2)

Use variables in config files.

Example: /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf.j2.

Conditionals & Loops

when: ansible_os_family == "Debian"
loop: "{{ packages }}"


Handlers

Triggered only when changed: true.

Example: restart service after config change.

Tags

Run specific tasks only.

ansible-playbook play.yml --tags "setup"


Vault

Encrypt sensitive data (passwords, keys).

ansible-vault encrypt secrets.yml
ansible-vault view secrets.yml


Roles

Best practice for reusable code.

Structure:

roles/
 â””â”€â”€ nginx/
     â”œâ”€â”€ tasks/
     â”œâ”€â”€ handlers/
     â”œâ”€â”€ templates/
     â”œâ”€â”€ files/
     â”œâ”€â”€ vars/
     â””â”€â”€ defaults/


âœ… Medium concepts prepare you for real team projects.

ğŸ”¹ 3ï¸âƒ£ Advanced Concepts (FAANG-Level)

Dynamic Inventory

AWS EC2 plugin â†’ aws_ec2.yaml.

GCP, Azure, Kubernetes inventory.

Error Handling

ignore_errors: yes

failed_when: custom conditions.

block, rescue, always.

Idempotency & Check Mode

ansible-playbook play.yml --check â†’ dry run.

changed_when: to define change detection.

Async & Parallel Execution

Run long tasks in background â†’ async, poll.

serial: control batch size.

Ansible Galaxy

Download & publish community roles.

ansible-galaxy install geerlingguy.nginx


Callbacks & Plugins

Callback plugins â†’ custom logging/output.

Lookup plugins â†’ fetch secrets, files, env vars.

Ansible Tower / AWX

Web UI + RBAC + job scheduling.

Enterprise-level CI/CD integration.

Testing

Molecule â†’ unit testing roles/playbooks.

ansible-lint â†’ style & syntax checks.

Performance

strategy: free â†’ tasks run as soon as possible.

fact_caching â†’ Redis, JSON, Memcached.

pipelining = True in ansible.cfg for speed.

Security

Vault + external secret managers (HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager).

Restricting SSH keys & sudo usage.

âœ… These are FAANG interviewer favorites.

ğŸ”¹ 4ï¸âƒ£ Real-World DevOps Scenarios

Provisioning â†’ Create users, install packages, configure firewalls.

App Deployment â†’ Deploy Nginx, Tomcat, Java apps.

CI/CD â†’ Jenkins pipeline triggers Ansible playbooks.

Hybrid Infra Mgmt â†’ Same playbook for on-prem + cloud.

Patching & Updates â†’ Run monthly patching across 1000+ servers.

Rolling Updates â†’ Update app servers one by one with serial: 1.

Secrets Mgmt â†’ Vault integration for DB passwords.

Immutable Infra â†’ Provision AMIs + configs before baking into Terraform.

Monitoring Setup â†’ Deploy Prometheus + Grafana agents via Ansible.

âœ… These scenarios prove hands-on experience.

